text: Pseudophilautus dimbullae is a frog. It lived in Sri Lanka. People have seen it in exactly one place: the Queenswood Estate in the Dimbulla Valley, 1500 meters above sea level. This frog is extinct. All frogs in this species are dead. One adult female frog was 44.8 mm long from nose to rear end. ==First paper== * ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Pseudophilautus dimbullae
